TOTAL: 49 + 3 magi   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">OK, it works sort of like this... burn burn burn.<br />
To be more technical cast some spells with Valkan take advantage of his pyromancy while he lives (this usually isn&#39;t very long) and set yourself up for Nara. Nara&#39;s Jiles and Ergars will prove a good defense because of her effect so you can use her as a stall while your energize keeps you strong and your hand builds up. Finally bring in Raega and clear out there monsters with cremate and clear the magis with your beasts, spells or whatever else you can throw at them. Most of the creatures in this deck have powers that can do some decent damage like the big bertha known as Fire Crag. I hope that this deck will work please review to tell me. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
